==English==
===Noun===
'''fug'''
#(''obscure'') A heavy, musty, and unpleasant [[atmosphere]].
#(''obscure'') The residual [[moisture]] (condensation of breath) caused by breathing on [[cold]] glass.

*Citation: ''The misty '''fug''' his breath had left on the window sparkled in the orange glare of the streetlamp outside ...'' -- '''''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince''''' (British edition), pg 42.